A Closer Look at GDP

First lets look at the relative distributions of GDP per capita across continents. Notice Ive dropped Oceania here because there are no observations for GDP in 1952 for that region. I also constrain the X axis because there was a single outlier that limited the visibility of the distributions when included.

One interesting feature of the data illustrated by this graph is that the African, American, and Asian continents all exhibit relatively uni-modal distributions of GDP per capita, while Europe has more variation or a multi-modal distribution.
